docs.abstract: The North Dakota senator, an endangered Democrat, ran an ad criticizing her opponent for comments about sexual abuse. But it backfired, just three weeks before the midterms.
docs.snippet: The North Dakota senator, an endangered Democrat, ran an ad criticizing her opponent for comments about sexual abuse. But it backfired, just three weeks before the midterms.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Heidi Heitkamp of North Dakota issued an apology on Tuesday for an ad her campaign ran that incorrectly identified victims of sexual abuse, throwing her uphill re-election bid further off balance just three weeks before the midterms.

headline.main: Heitkamp Apologizes for Embarrassing Error in Campaign Ad

docs.abstract: The Republican nominee for Senate in Virginia likes to engage the racial fringes of his party, creating a dilemma for mainstream G.O.P. leaders wary of his views.
docs.snippet: The Republican nominee for Senate in Virginia likes to engage the racial fringes of his party, creating a dilemma for mainstream G.O.P. leaders wary of his views.
docs.lead_paragraph: WOODBRIDGE, Va. — Corey Stewart stands at the end of a long driveway that leads back in time, to his 18th century plantation manor hidden in woods behind a modern housing development. Mr. Stewart, the Republican Senate nominee from Virginia, treats the brick home like a living museum, complete with buttons from Redcoats, a Civil War soldier’s belt buckle and a room dedicated to George and Martha Washington, who were once visitors.

headline.main: White Nationalists Love Corey Stewart. He Keeps Them Close.
headline.print_headline: Favored by White Nationalists, Candidate Keeps Them Close
